10. What is Concurrency Control in Power Automate?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ Concurrency Control helps you manage how many simultaneous (parallel) flow runs can happen at the same time. 
   â€” especially important when working with loops (Apply to each).

ğŸ”¹ Why It's Needed:
ğŸ‘‰ When a loop processes many items (e.g., SharePoint list items, array values), Power Automate runs iterations in parallel by default.
ğŸ”¹ This can:
ğŸ‘‰ Improve performance âœ…
ğŸ‘‰ But also cause data conflicts, race conditions âŒ (e.g., when updating same record or sending multiple dependent actions)

ğŸ”§ How to Enable/Disable:
ğŸ‘‰ In your flow, go to "Apply to each" â†’ Click ellipsis (...)
ğŸ‘‰ Choose "Settings"
ğŸ‘‰ You'll see a setting:
ğŸ”˜ Concurrency Control â†’ Turn it On
ğŸ‘‰ Set Degree of Parallelism (e.g., 1 to 50)





